profile_positions.description:
1. Responsible for the overall operation and management of the European HRBP Department. 
2. Responsible for Human Resource Strategic Planning, Recruitment and Selection, Performance Appraisal, C&B Management, Employee Incentives, Training and Development, Employee Relations & Organization Environment, Handbook and Employee Contract etc.
•	Responsible for formulating, improving and implementing company's HR Management Mechanism, such as Salary Management System, Performance Evaluation Methodology, Labor Contract and Handbook, as well as Recruitment Management;
•	Responsible for training development, enhance business knowledge and ability;
•	Cooperate with the heads of each department for talent development and training;
•	Liaise with 21 country managers on HR domain improvement in each country (such as Employee Benefits, Contract, Performance Evaluation Methodology etc.)

Responsibilities:
•Work Force Plan( HC control): 
Based on the headcount from the previous year, set up a kick-off meeting between management team and BU s, finalize action plan on external recruitment and internal transfer.
•Organizational Atmosphere( Employee Relationship Management)：
a)Communication Mechanism: Such as  a F2F talk between employee and the head of VEON KAD; Between Management Team and all BU s, and between HRBP and  employees, streamline the highlight from the talk with employees and discussed during the management meeting;
b)Organizational report analysis and improvement plan apply;
c)All kinds of activities, such as team-buildings, festivals and birthdays etc.
•Performance Business Commitment: Lead employees to work on Performance assessment and quality control; and analyze the report from HQ regarding Performance Management and set up an improvement plan;
•Recruitment: Externally, co-operate with Headhunting companies to search for the right candidates, provide end to end service, internally, through i-job system to recruitment employees from different regional within Huawei;
•Training: Create training opportunities for employees internally according to business needs; Such as Reserve Resource, bi-weekly training etc.
•Incentive: OTE and TUP guiding, till signing, Excellent Employees and Subsidiary publication and Award of Galloping Horses etc.
•Contract Management and Termination: 
a)Employee contract sighing and extension process etc., end to end service;
b)Together with the Netherlands HR working on Contract Termination, such as Negotiation, Severance Package related.
•Other daily work, such as Competence and Qualification guidance, Visa issue control (5 years policy application) and Labor Law propaganda etc.

•	Customer Voice and Complaint Management etc. through icare and CESM system, and ITR(issue to resolution) promotion within 19 countries;
•	Scorecard(Customer side) and 3rd Party Survey report analysis for providing improvement plan which is aligned with each subsidiary(19 countries);
•	Weekly meeting presentation(PPT) and improvement plan status track;
•	Liaise with HQ and Subsidiary to fulfill the front-line needs and appeals
•	Monthly delivery report to HQ Shenzhen and Asia/Africa Customers and semi-yearly &yearly report.
•	Responsible for the editing of the Monthly Service Magazine Edition

•          Involved in MV-SPMS(Rome),Algeria 2G&3G rollout(Algiers) and Power Supply System project tender
